<header class="hero">
  <div class="eyebrow">The Five Points Examined</div>
  <h1>Understanding TULIP</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">A Biblical Examination of the Five Points of Calvinism</p>
  <p class="lede">
    TULIP summarizes the five central doctrines that emerged from the Synod of Dort
    and have become a defining expression of Reformed soteriology.
  </p>
  <div class="divider"></div>
</header>

<section class="intro">
  <p>
    This section explains each doctrine as Calvinists themselves understand it,
    before examining the biblical evidence, the historical context, and the
    principal objections raised by non-Calvinist Christians.
  </p>
  <div class="goal-box">
    <p>
      Our goal is not to caricature Calvinism, but to present each point fairly
      and evaluate whether it reflects the whole counsel of Scripture.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="explore">
  <div class="explore-heading">
    <h2>Explore Each Doctrine</h2>
    <div class="rule"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="tulip-grid">

    <a href="total-depravity.html" class="doctrine-card">
      <div class="letter-badge">T</div>
      <div class="card-text">
        <h3>Total Depravity <span class="term">— T</span></h3>
        <p>Can spiritually dead sinners respond to God's call, or must regeneration precede faith?</p>
      </div>
      <span class="card-arrow">&rarr;</span>
    </a>

    <a href="unconditional-election.html" class="doctrine-card">
      <div class="letter-badge">U</div>
      <div class="card-text">
        <h3>Unconditional Election <span class="term">— U</span></h3>
        <p>Does God choose individuals for salvation apart from any response of faith?</p>
      </div>
      <span class="card-arrow">&rarr;</span>
    </a>

    <a href="limited-atonement.html" class="doctrine-card">
      <div class="letter-badge">L</div>
      <div class="card-text">
        <h3>Limited Atonement <span class="term">— L</span></h3>
        <p>Did Christ die only for the elect, or for the sins of the whole world?</p>
      </div>
      <span class="card-arrow">&rarr;</span>
    </a>

    <a href="irresistible-grace.html" class="doctrine-card">
      <div class="letter-badge">I</div>
      <div class="card-text">
        <h3>Irresistible Grace <span class="term">— I</span></h3>
        <p>Can God's saving grace be resisted, or is every person whom God calls inevitably brought to faith?</p>
      </div>
      <span class="card-arrow">&rarr;</span>
    </a>

    <a href="perseverance-of-the-saints.html" class="doctrine-card">
      <div class="letter-badge">P</div>
      <div class="card-text">
        <h3>Perseverance of the Saints <span class="term">— P</span></h3>
        <p>Does every true believer inevitably persevere to the end &mdash; and what does Scripture actually teach about assurance and perseverance?</p>
      </div>
      <span class="card-arrow">&rarr;</span>
    </a>

  </div>

  <div class="footer-note">
    <p>&ldquo;Test everything; hold fast what is good.&rdquo; &mdash; 1 Thessalonians 5:21</p>
  </div>
</section>

